title: 15 MIN EXPRESS PILATES WORKOUT || Dynamic Intermediate Pilates (No Equipment)
description:
Get ready to move with this Express Pilates Workout. This class is dynamic and fast-paced so don't worry if you have to do it a few times to get the feel of it. Have fun! 😊

🤍 ¿Hablas español? Subscribe to my Spanish YouTube Channel.
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCnUpf4yc9TYkmhFUq4cbJoA

🌸 Mat from Liforme - https://liforme.com/
Use my code 'MOVEWITHNICOLEYOGA' for a discount.


🤍 INSTAGRAM: @movewithnicole


🎥 Videography by Bodie Rex
♫ Music from https://www.epidemicsound.com/referral/n9a93q/

channelDescription:
Hi, I'm Nicole! 😊 I am a Certified Pilates & Certified Yoga Instructor (RYT 500) with many years of in-studio teaching experience. As a former dancer and gymnast, I have always had a passion for movement and I love being able to share that passion with others. I believe in finding forms of movement that feel good for your body and soul and I hope that through my classes, I can guide you to your best feeling self!

--
I was a professional Latin Ballroom Dancer and taught Ballroom dancing to adults for 7+ years. This is truly where I established my passion for teaching movement. When I retired from competitive dancing in 2017, I began teaching Barre and Pilates in studios and gyms in Sydney.

During COVID lockdown, Dance & Pilates studios closed and that was when I poured my love of teaching into this channel, hoping to help people keep moving and feeling good!

Thank you so much for practicing with me and I hope you enjoy the classes as much as I love creating them for you. 🩷

comments: Oh boy - this workout embodies "tiny but MIGHTY!" Don't let the "15 mins express" title fool you. This will give you a burning but totally rewarding sweat!!
I don’t know how you can kill me in 18 minutes-but THANK YOU. You have changed my life Nicole❤️🔥

Love your classes. Please add more 10 min stretch and 15-20 min Pilates and yoga flow videos. I don’t have enough time for the longer ones and don’t like to stop mid stream and not finish out the workout without a wind down and final zen moment. Thank you for your time and efforts. You are greatly appreciated.❤

Some of these moves can be really challenging, so I tell myself: If Mick Jagger can do yoga and pilates at 80, so can I at 46. 😁💪 Thank you Nicole for keeping us motivated and for always reminding us on a correct breathing technique.😊

Thank you, Nicole, for all of your amazing classes! I started doing them in the beginning of the year, and now I do them as part of my daily routine and I feel better both physically and mentally because of them. It's one of the things in my day that I truly look forward to!  Thank you! 😀
